      "ocrText": "'B Study the infographic and read the dialogue. Then, answer the questions that\nfollow.\n2 HOW TO BE TSUNAMI READY\nZs\n70 =~ A tsunami is a series of huge waves caused by strong\n~~ 122 et earthquakes. Those living in coastal areas like Langkawi and\nVoy les, Penang Island are at risk of tsunamis.\nWARNING SIGNS TO WATCH OUT FOR\nul —\n(RJR\n3 Lee rene 13 2 ih i) A .\nPl — INN 2590 0 ng\nIC was 7 \\ an\nAll| [FE es\nA strong quake that lasts Rise or fall in sea level Animals behaving strangely.\nfor more than a minute such as dogs howling and\n) birds flying away in flocks\n« If you see these warning signs, get away from where you are. Go as far inland as\nyou can and as high ground as possible.\n« Know the tsunami evacuation zones in your area.\nFor more information on how to be tsunami ready, log on to ;\n< www.tsunamiready.com\nNaveen : What's the infographic about?\nYew Keong: It's about being prepared for a tsunami. There's been quite a few\n~ earthquakes in neighbouring Indonesia. Remember last week when we\nfelt some tremors?\nNaveen  : That was terrifying. I was asleep and woke up when I felt my bed shaking.\nYew Keong: I was just about to turn in for the night when I felt it. My night lamp shook\nand fell to the floor.\nNaveen : We couldn't sleep anymore afterwards. I remember my dad checking his\nsmartphone for updates to see if there were any tsunami warnings.\nYew Keong: Mine too. We always have a bag packed with clothes, water and food on\nstandby. We have to be prepared as we live near the beach.\nNaveen : Let's look up more information on how to be tsunami ready on the website\nsuggested in the library after school today.\n7 © EPH Publishing (M) Sdn. Bhd.\n{Scanned with\ni [cs] CamScanner’|",
